{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, agents can communicate more specific information, such as in GAXNet [79], where agents coordinate their local attention weights, integrating hidden states from neighboring agents.",
    "Messages can also be modeled as random variables, as seen in NDQ [74], where messages are drawn from a multivariate Gaussian distribution to maximize expressiveness by maximizing mutual information between messages and receivers' action selection.",
    "In learning tasks with emergent language, agents often communicate goal-related information, such as the goal's location [60][61][62][63][64].",
    "Imagined future knowledgeIn this context, Imagined Future Knowledge refers to aspects such as intended actions [38], policy fingerprints (i.e., action probabilities in a given state) [83,84], or future plans [89].",
    "Since intentions are related to the current environment state, recent works often combine intended actions with local observations to produce more relevant messages."
  ]
}